The paper deals with the problem of constructing binary codes for correcting deletions, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes new explicit codes with efficient encoding and decoding algorithms, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the generalized version of the problem, which involves deletions localized within multiple windows, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR) and signal processing (cs.SI).
